This paper deals with natural language processing and semantic parsing, which are core topics in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of neural networks and attention mechanisms also suggests that this paper could be relevant to the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of ontology databases and SPARQL queries, which are related to the field of databases (cs.DB). The use of neural networks for encoding and decoding also suggests that this paper could be relevant to the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves the generation of queries, which is related to the field of information retrieval (cs.IR).
